{
  "texts": [
    "Relative RA (µas) can be used to evaluate the success of our imaging methods by quantitatively reproducing the non-ring synthetic data sets such as the disk and the double source.",
    "Figure 13 shows the ring parameters (diameter d, width w, and position angle) measured with REx and VIDA for all bands, days, and imaging pipelines for HOPS and CASA data reconstructions.",
    "On April 21, all bands and pipelines show ring-like structures with a roughly consistent diameter of ∼42 µas as expected from the image morphology discussed in Sect. 5.2.",
    "Position angle values are around 215 • and are consistent among all bands and pipelines for April 21.",
    "Width measurements have relatively large differences among the imaging pipelines, especially between DIFMAP and the other methods."
  ]
}